// ward-kdl ops forgejo-key - read ONLY the Forgejo API token from the k3s
// external-secrets mirror through kubectl (cli-guard execverb, exec dialect).
// This is the non-2FA path to the token: external-secrets mirrors
// /forgejo/api-token (SSM) into the `forgejo-runner-secrets` Secret (key
// `api-token`, namespace `forgejo`) using static AWS creds, so a scoped kubectl
// reader over the tailnet reaches it without an AWS call or a 2FA prompt
// (ward#386). The single `read` grant pins the ENTIRE kubectl invocation with an
// `argv` override and then seals it against any caller expansion:
//
//   - `deny-when any-arg matches "*"` refuses every trailing positional, so the
//     caller can never append another resource/secret name.
//   - `allow-flag` names one impossible sentinel flag, making the flag policy a
//     strict allowlist that admits nothing - every real caller flag (`-n`, `-o`,
//     `--namespace`, `--kubeconfig`, ...) is refused, so a namespace/output-format
//     pivot is blocked.
//
// Together these two guards are the interim spelling of the `sealed` clause
// (cli-guard#173): freeze the argv, forbid trailing caller tokens. When that
// sugar lands upstream this collapses to a single `sealed` line. The
// `go-template` with `base64decode` decodes the token in-line, matching the old
// `ssm get-parameter --output text` behaviour. The key `api-token` carries a
// hyphen, so it is read with `index .data "api-token"` - dotted field access
// (`.data.api-token`) is invalid Go-template syntax. Every call audit-logs
// through ward like any other ops verb.
// See ../../docs/ward-kdl/ward-kdl.forgejo-key.guardfile.md.
wrap ward-kdl ops forgejo-key {
    exec kubectl
    can run read {
        argv get secret forgejo-runner-secrets -n forgejo -o "go-template={{index .data \"api-token\" | base64decode}}"
        // seal the argv: no trailing positionals, no caller flags (see header).
        deny-when any-arg matches *
        allow-flag --ward-sealed-single-key
        describe "read ONLY the forgejo api-token from the k3s external-secrets mirror, decoded"
    }
}
